		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} invests in Danish cultural institutions and conservation of historic sites.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>Odin Owns Us All</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_HELP">
			<Text>Your helm and axe, High Thane! A rabble approaches the palace, drunk on fire. They say you must give in to their political or be deposed![NEWLINE]You would have thought they would know better than to challenge the great Bluetooth!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Receive a Great Person of your choice.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>Introduce Longhouses for {1_YieldCost}, which upgrade Barracks to generate an additional +2 [ICON_FOOD] Food and +2 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Move away from stone Temples to Stave Churches from the plentiful resource of wood. Temple pay for their maintenance, repay +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production per turn and generate +1 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>The policy of naval dominance causes Harbours and Castles to yield +1 [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age Points, and for Citadels to yield +3 [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age Points.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_HELP_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>A Guerilla is recruited in every City. The new military expansion allows Cities to generate +3 [ICON_PRODUCTION] for every Snow tile in workable range.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_HELP_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>Spend {1_YieldCost} promoting Danish culture. Writers' Guilds increase [ICON_CULTURE] Culture generation by 15%. Jelling Stones generate +2 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>I haven't fought a good single combat in many moons. Come, there must be a Great Man amongst them who will challenge me!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*Many gathered outside the Palace are desperate, having no reliable shelter in which to endure the winter months*[NEWLINE]What good are strong warriors when we cannot protect our people from the cold? Open up the Barracks and put our men to work constructing homes becoming of Danes.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*The masses are angered by your apparent disrespect for the Gods, and wish to see more Temples*[NEWLINE]I do what I can to honour the Gods, it is regrettable that we cannot do more. From this day, I will begin a new building project, to erect a new kind of church! They shall stand in every community, a symbol of our culture.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*The minor Cities of the world continue to slight our rule of the seas. The demonstrators demand you establish unquestionable dominance.*[NEWLINE]The rabble and I are in agreement. The seas belong to the Danes!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>*The public are concerned about the cost of war. If you cannot quickly end the conflict, they demand you step down.*[NEWLINE]The war is fought on all fronts, but there are skills we Danes know that the enemy does not. I will announce our new initiative to the amassed crowd.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_DENMARK_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>*The public are angry at what they consider the complacency of the Palace to promote alternatives to warfare.*[NEWLINE]Long has our culture revolved around war. For once we have the opportunity to reflect on the other parts of our history. I will see this wish made flesh in a great celebration of Danish culture.</Text>
		</Row>

		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_DENMARK_UE_DUMMY">
			<Text></Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
